      <description>&lt;figure&gt;&#xD;&#xA;      &lt;img class=&#34;my-0 rounded-md&#34; src=&#34;featured.jpg&#34; alt=&#34;&#34; /&gt;&#xD;&#xA;  &#xD;&#xA;  &#xD;&#xA;  &lt;/figure&gt;&#xA;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;h2 class=&#34;relative group&#34;&gt;Background Knowledge&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;div id=&#34;background-knowledge&#34; class=&#34;anchor&#34;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &#xD;&#xA;    &lt;span&#xD;&#xA;        class=&#34;absolute top-0 w-6 transition-opacity opacity-0 -start-6 not-prose group-hover:opacity-100 select-none&#34;&gt;&#xD;&#xA;        &lt;a class=&#34;text-primary-300 dark:text-neutral-700 !no-underline&#34; href=&#34;#background-knowledge&#34; aria-label=&#34;Anchor&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;/span&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &#xD;&#xA;&lt;/h2&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;This writeup is for &lt;code&gt;Cupids Matchmaker&lt;/code&gt;, a room in TryHackMe (THM) for Valentine&amp;rsquo;s 2026 Event. This room focuses on XSS Vulnerability.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;XXS is a condition when your browser can run a javascript code written by users injected through user inputs. This usually happens when inputs aren&amp;rsquo;t sanitized and are directly run by the code. There are 3 types of XXS, they are Stored, Reflected, and Blind XXS.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
      
